sentences: Florentín Giménez (14 March 1925 – 11 March 2021) was a Paraguayan pianist and composer.

In 1945, at the age of 20, he learned to play the piano and became a pianist in Ramón Reyes’ Orchestra, where he stayed until 1947, when the Paraguayan Civil War forced him to leave the country and settle in Argentina.

In 1945, at the age of 20, he learned to play the piano and became a pianist in Ramón Reyes’ Orchestra, where he stayed until 1947, when the Paraguayan Civil War forced him to leave the country and settle in Argentina.
In 1950, he formed the 14-member orchestra “Florentín Giménez y su típica Moderna”, which featured singers Oscar Escobar, Juan Carlos Miranda, Carlos Centurión, and Jorge Alonso.
Because of his protests against the government, Giménez was labeled a communist and arrested in 1953.
He was jailed for several months.
He died from COVID-19 during the COVID-19 pandemic in Paraguay, three days short from his 96th birthday.
